{"lemma":"باطِلٌ","slug":"باطِلٌ","root":"ب.ط.ل","root_slug":"ب-ط-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ط-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"باطِل","root":"بطل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":26},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2793"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%90%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"false","examples":[{"text":"اِتِّهَامٌ بَاطِلٌ","english":"false accusation"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"vain"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"useless"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"invalid, null and void"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"invalid"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"falsehood","examples":[{"text":"مَا أُسِّسَ عَلَى بَاطِلٍ فَهُوَ بَاطِلٌ."},{"text":"جَاءَ الْحَقُّ وَزَهَقَ الْبَاطِلُ إِنَّ الْبَاطِلَ كَانَ زَهُوقًا"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wrong, injustice","examples":[{"text":"وَلَا تَأْكُلُوا أَمْوَالَكُمْ بَيْنَكُمْ بِالْبَاطِلِ وَتُدْلُوا بِهَا إِلَى الْحُكَّامِ لِتَأْكُلُوا فَرِيقًا مِنْ أَمْوَالِ النَّاسِ بِالْإِثْمِ وَأَنْتُمْ تَعْلَمُونَ"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb بَطَلَ (baṭala, “to be vain, to be false”)."},"ipa":["/baː.tˤil/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2793","headword_ar":"بَاطِلٌ","root":"bTl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haq~N","text_ar":"حَقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"False, untrue, wrong"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incorrect, fictitious, spurious, unfounded, unsound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, unreal, naught, futile, worthless, useless, unprofitable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL, PS,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devoid of virtue"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"efficacy, ineffectual, null, void, of no force,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of no effect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that proves, when inquired into,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"investigated, to be false, wrong, unfounded, unsound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not established;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applying to a saying, and [sometimes] to a deed: (TA:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"going for nothing, as a thing of no account,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a thing that has perished"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"become lost:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see the verb, 1, first sentence:) often used as a subst., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, saying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assertion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allegation; a lie; a falsehood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"action,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTolN","text_ar":"بُطْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. therewith, (Ham p. 114,) and so are ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uboTuwlapN","text_ar":"اُبْطُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iboTaAlapN","text_ar":"اـِبْطَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATilN","text_ar":"بَاطِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bawaATilu","text_ar":"بَوَاطِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTulN","text_ar":"بُطُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs as a pl. of the same; (Ham p. 360;) or its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaATiylu","text_ar":"اَبَاطِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", contr. to analogy, (S, Msb,) as though the sing. were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iboTiylN","text_ar":"اـِبْطِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or, accord. to AHát, this is pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uboTuwlapN","text_ar":"اُبْطُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or, as some say, of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iboTaAlapN","text_ar":"اـِبْطَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or, accord. to As and AHát and IDrd, of both these; (TA;) and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, sayings"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"actions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deeds."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"htr","text_ar":"هتر"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado qulota baATilFA","text_ar":"قَدْ قُلْتَ بَاطِلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast said a false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, saying; a lie; a falsehood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado qulota Haq~FA","text_ar":"قَدْ قُلْتَ حَقًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Ham p. 360.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA^okuluwna A^amowaAla Aln~aAsi biAlbaATili","text_ar":"يَاْكُلُونَ اَمْوَالَ النَّاسِ بِالبَاطِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They devour the possessions of men by false pretence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Kur ix. 34.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumo A^uboTuwlapN","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمْ اُبْطُولَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iboTaAlapN","text_ar":"اـِبْطَالَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between them is false,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discourse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATilN","text_ar":"بَاطِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belief in a plurality of Gods:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so explained as occurring in the Kur xlii. 23. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baT~aAlN","text_ar":"بَطَّالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATilFA","text_ar":"بَاطِلًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In play,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sport; acting unprofitably;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aiming at no profit."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in iii. 188 and xxxviii. 26.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaATilu","text_ar":"البَاطِلُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Iblees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur [xxxiv. 48], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA yubodiy^u A@lobaATilu","text_ar":"مَا يُبْدِيُ ا@لْبَاطِلُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa maA yuEiydu","text_ar":"وَ مَا يُعِيدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bdA^","text_ar":"بدا"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Katádeh, K:) and again [xli. 42], where it is said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yaA^otiyhi","text_ar":"لَا يَاْتِيهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@lobaATilu mino bayona yadayohi wa laA mino xalofihi","text_ar":"ا@لْبَاطِلُ مِنْ بَيْنَ يَدَيْهِ وَ لَا مِنْ خَلْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [accord. to some,] meaning that Iblees shall not add to the Kur-án nor diminish therefrom: (TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTalapN","text_ar":"بَطَلَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is its pl., and] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devils:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"enchanters."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["KL","PS","TA","K","S","Msb","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%84/","headword_ar":"باطل","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23004#dd6316","body_html":"<span>الباطل: هو الذي لا يكون صحيحًا بأصله.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23004#7ec30c","body_html":"<span>الباطل: ما لا يعتد به، ولا يفيد شيئًا.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_18","lexicon_en":"Al-Sharīf al-Jurjānī, Kitāb al-Taʿrīfāt (d. 1413 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب التعريفات للشريف الجرجاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=23004#eb21b0","body_html":"<span>الباطل: ما كان فائت المعنى من كل وجه، مع وجود الصورة؛ إما لانعدام الأهلية أو المحلية، كبيع الحر، وبيع الصبي.</span>"}]}}